 King Williams Town - Kei Bridge police are investigating a case of a missing person and have appealed to the public to come forward with any information that might be able to assist them in their search. "It is alleged that a 17-year-old girl, Nasiphi Xelanto, was last seen on Monday, 06 January 2020, at her home by her mother," said police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni. "The daughter and the mother had a misunderstanding. "The 17-year-old girl left her home situated at Deyi Locality, Ngquthu Village near Kei Bridge, Butterworth." Capt Tonjeni said that she was last seen wearing maroon straight cut skirt, white polo neck, white socks, light blue hooded jersey and black half boots. "Anyone who may know of her whereabouts is kindly requested to contact Kei Bridge Police on Station at 043 831 2018." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 